ary autosomal recessive microcephaly and a novel CDK5RAP2 mutation|url=http://ojrd.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1750-1172-8-59|journal=Orphanet Journal of Rare Diseases|language=en|volume=8|issue=1|pages=59|doi=10.1186/1750-1172-8-59|issn=1750-1172|pmc=3639195|pmid=23587236}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kalasova|first=Ilona|last2=Hanzlikova|first2=Hana|last3=Gupta|first3=Neerja|last4=Li|first4=Yun|last5=Altm\u00fcller|first5=Janine|last6=Reynolds|first6=John J.|last7=Stewart|first7=Grant S.|last8=Wollnik|first8=Bernd|last9=Yigit|first9=G\u00f6khan|last10=Caldecott|first10=Keith W.|date=2019|title=Novel PNKP mutations causing defective DNA strand break repair and PARP1 hyperactivity in MCSZ|url=http://ng.neurology.org/lookup/doi/10.1212/NXG.0000000000000320|journal=Neurol Genet|language=en|volume=5|issue=2|pages=e320|doi=10.1212/NXG.0000000000000320|issn=2376-7839|pmc=PMC6454307|pmid=31041400|via=}}</ref> with microcephaly, seizures and defects in DNA repair. A type of recessive ataxia is also associated with PNKP mutations.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bras|first=Jose|last2=Alonso|first2=Isabel|last3=Barbot|first3=Clara|last4=Costa|first4=Maria\u00a0Manuela|last5=Darwent|first5=Lee|last6=Orme|first6=Tatiana|last7=Sequeiros|first7=Jorge|last8=Hardy|first8=John|last9=Coutinho|first9=Paula|last10=Guerreiro|first10=Rita|date=2015|title=Mutations in PNKP Cause Recessive Ataxia with Oculomotor Apraxia Type 4|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0002929715000130|journal=The American Journal of Human Genetics|language=en|volume=96|issue=3|pages=474\u2013479|doi=10.1016/j.ajhg.2015.01.005|pmc=4375449|pmid=25728773|via=}}</ref> There are also newly characterized pathological variants of PNKP.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gatti|first=Marta|last2=Magri|first2=Stefania|last3=Nanetti|first3=Lorenzo|last4=Sarto|first4=Elisa|last5=Di Bella|first5=Daniela|last6=Salsano|first6=Ettore|last7=Pantaleoni|first7=Chiara|last8=Mariotti|first8=Caterina|last9=Taroni|first9=Franco|