leotide kinase participates in repair of DNA double-strand breaks by nonhomologous end joining but not homologous recombination | journal = Cancer Res. | volume = 67 | issue = 14 | pages = 6619\u201325 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17638872 | doi = 10.1158/0008-5472.CAN-07-0480 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Mani RS, Fanta M, Karimi-Busheri F, Silver E, Virgen CA, Caldecott KW, Cass CE, Weinfeld M | title = XRCC1 stimulates polynucleotide kinase by enhancing its damage discrimination and displacement from DNA repair intermediates | journal = J. Biol. Chem. | volume = 282 | issue = 38 | pages = 28004\u201313 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17650498 | doi = 10.1074/jbc.M704867200 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{PDB Gallery|geneid=11284}}\n\n\n{{gene-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "<br />{{Infobox_gene}}\n'''Bifunctional polynucleotide phosphatase/kinase''' is an [[enzyme]] that in humans is encoded by the ''PNKP'' [[gene]].<ref name=\"pmid10446192\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Jilani A, Ramotar D, Slack C, Ong C, Yang XM, Scherer SW, Lasko DD | title = Molecular cloning of the human gene, PNKP, encoding a polynucleotide kinase 3'-phosphatase and evidence for its role in repair of DNA strand breaks caused by oxidative damage | journal = J. Biol. Chem. | volume = 274 | issue = 34 | pages = 24176\u201386  | date = September 1999 | pmid = 10446192 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1074/jbc.274.34.24176 }}</ref><ref name=\"pmid10446193\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Karimi-Busheri F, Daly G, Robins P, Canas B, Pappin DJ, Sgouros J, Miller GG, Fakhrai H, Davis EM, Le Beau MM, Weinfeld M | title = Molecular characterization of a human DNA kinase | journal = J. Biol. Chem. | volume = 274 | issue = 34 | pages = 24187\u201394  | date = September 1999 | pmid = 10446193 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1074/jbc.274.34.24187 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: PNKP polynucleotide kinase 3'-phosphatase| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=11284| accessdate = }}</ref>\n\n== Interactions ==\n\nPNKP has been shown to [[Protein-protein interaction|interact]] with [[DNA polymerase beta]]<ref name=pmid11163244>{{cite journal | vauthors = Whitehouse CJ, Taylor RM, Thistlethwaite A, Zhang H, Karimi-Busheri F, Lasko DD, Weinfeld M, Caldecott KW | title = XRCC1 stimulates human polynucleotide kinase activity at damaged DNA termini and accelerates DNA single-strand break repair | journal = Cell | volume = 104 | issue = 1 | pages = 107\u201317  | date = January 2001 | pmid = 11163244 | doi = 10.1016/S0092-8674(01)00195-7 }}</ref> and [[XRCC1]].<ref name=pmid11163244/><ref name=pmid17353931>{{cite journal | vauthors = Ewing RM, Chu P, Elisma F, Li H, Taylor P, Climie S, McBroom-Cerajewski L, Robinson MD, O'Connor L, Li M, Taylor R, Dharsee M, Ho Y, Heilbut A, Moore L, Zhang S, Ornatsky O, Bukhman YV, Ethier M, Sheng Y, Vasilescu J, Abu-Farha M, Lambert JP, Duewel HS, Stewart II, Kuehl B, Hogue K, Colwill K, Gladwish K, Muskat B, Kinach R, Adams SL, Moran MF, Morin GB, Topaloglou T, Figeys D | title = Large-scale mapping of human protein-protein interactions by mass spectrometry | journal = Mol. Syst. Biol. | volume = 3 | issue = 1 | pages = 89 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17353931 | pmc = 1847948 | doi = 10.1038/msb4100134 }}</ref>\n\n== Role in Neurologic Disease<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Dumitrache|first=Lavinia C.|last2=McKinnon|first2=Peter J.|date=2017|title=Polynucleotide kinase-phosphatase (PNKP) mutations and neurologic disease|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0047637416300513|journal=Mechanisms of Ageing and Development|language=en|volume=161|pages=121\u2013129|doi=10.1016/j.mad.2016.04.009|pmc=5161711|pmid=27125728|via=}}</ref>==\n\nThe human gene encoding PNKP was observed to be mutated in patients <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Shen|first=Jun|last2=Gilmore|first2=Edward C|last3=Marshall|first3=Christine A|last4=Haddadin|first4=Mary|last5=Reynolds|first5=John J|last6=Eyaid|first6=Wafaa|last7=Bodell|first7=Adria|last8=Barry|first8=Brenda|last9=Gleason|first9=Danielle|last10=Allen|first10=Kathryn|last11=Ganesh|first11=Vijay S|date=2010|title=Mutations in PNKP cause microcephaly, seizures and defects in DNA repair|url=http://www.nature.com/articles/ng.526|journal=Nat Genet|language=en|volume=42|issue=3|pages=245\u2013249|doi=10.1038/ng.526|issn=1061-4036|pmc=2835984|pmid=20118933|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Issa|first=Lina|last2=Mueller|first2=Katrin|last3=Seufert|first3=Katja|last4=Kraemer|first4=Nadine|last5=Rosenkotter|first5=Henning|last6=Ninnemann|first6=Olaf|last7=Buob|first7=Michael|last8=Kaindl|first8=Angela M|last9=Morris-Rosendahl|first9=Deborah J|date=2013|title=Clinical and cellular features in patients with primary autosomal recessive microcephaly and a novel CDK5RAP2 mutation|url=http://ojrd.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1750-1172-8-59|journal=Orphanet Journal of Rare Diseases|language=en|volume=8|issue=1|pages=59|doi=10.1186/1750-1172-8-59|issn=1750-1172|pmc=3639195|pmid=23587236}}</ref> with microcephaly, seizures and defects in DNA repair. A type of recessive ataxia is also associated with PNKP mutations.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bras|first=Jose|last2=Alonso|first2=Isabel|last3=Barbot|first3=Clara|last4=Costa|first4=Maria\u00a0Manuela|last5=Darwent|first5=Lee|last6=Orme|first6=Tatiana|last7=Sequeiros|first7=Jorge|last8=Hardy|first8=John|last9=Coutinho|first9=Paula|last10=Guerreiro|first10=Rita|date=2015|title=Mutations in PNKP Cause Recessive Ataxia with Oculomotor Apraxia Type 4|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0002929715000130|journal=The American Journal of Human Genetics|language=en|volume=96|issue=3|pages=474\u2013479|doi=10.1016/j.ajhg.2015.01.005|pmc=4375449|pmid=25728773|via=}}</ref> There are also newly characterized pathological variants of PNKP.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gatti|first=Marta|last2=Magri|first2=Stefania|last3=Nanetti|first3=Lorenzo|last4=Sarto|first4=Elisa|last5=Di Bella|first5=Daniela|last6=Salsano|first6=Ettore|last7=Pantaleoni|first7=Chiara|last8=Mariotti|first8=Caterina|last9=Taroni|first9=Franco|date=2019|title=From congenital microcephaly to adult onset cerebellar ataxia: Distinct and overlapping phenotypes in patients with PNKP gene mutations|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/ajmg.a.61339|journal=American Journal of Medical Genetics Part A|language=en|volume=179|issue=11|pages=2277\u20132283|doi=10.1002/ajmg.a.61339|issn=1552-4825|via=}}</ref> Model organisms such as mice and Drosophila have been used to generate further insights.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Shimada|first=Mikio|last2=Dumitrache|first2=Lavinia C|last3=Russell|first3=Helen R|last4=McKinnon|first4=Peter J|date=2015|title=Polynucleotide kinase\u2013phosphatase enables neurogenesis via multiple DNA repair pathways to maintain genome stability|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.15252/embj.201591363|journal=The EMBO Journal|language=en|volume=34|issue=19|pages=2465\u20132480|doi=10.15252/embj.201591363|issn=0261-4189|pmc=4601665|pmid=26290337|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Chakraborty|first=Anirban|last2=Tapryal|first2=Nisha|last3=Venkova|first3=Tatiana|last4=Mitra|first4=Joy|last5=Vasquez|first5=Velmarini|last6=Sarker|first6=Altaf H.|last7=Duarte-Silva|first7=Sara|last8=Huai|first8=Weihan|last9=Ashizawa|first9=Tetsuo|last10=Ghosh|first10=Gourisankar|last11=Maciel|first11=Patricia|date=2020-04-07|title=Deficiency in classical nonhomologous end-joining\u2013mediated repair of transcribed genes is linked to SCA3 pathogenesis|url=http://www.pnas.org/lookup/doi/10.1073/pnas.1917280117|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|language=en|volume=117|issue=14|pages=8154\u20138165|doi=10.1073/pnas.1917280117|issn=0027-8424}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin | 2}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Whitehouse CJ, Taylor RM, Thistlethwaite A, Zhang H, Karimi-Busheri F, Lasko DD, Weinfeld M, Caldecott KW | title = XRCC1 stimulates human 